  "text": "So far, ERKs have been profoundly studied [CITATION_1] , but the respective functions of JNK and its domains remain unclear. Several reports demonstrated that the effect of JNK on p53 in both normal cells and those exposed to external stresses. The association of JNK with p53 could efficiently inhibit p53 ubiquitination and this process is Mdm2 independent [CITATION_2] . In order to elucidate the regulation of p53 by effective domains of JNK, a NIH 3T3/Tetoff inducible expression system was established, and the C-JNK (aa 203-424) positive clones were selected by G418 and hygromycin. By removing tetracycline, we studied its effect on stability and transcription activity of p53 as well as cell growth.",
